{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013EH87vxP1F8aeYoutYguSL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's a summary of what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had write and read permissions on the `/app` vhost but the configure permission was empty. Declaring a queue requires configure permission in RabbitMQ, so every attempt by the producer to `PUT /api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` returned `{\"error\":\"not_authorised\",\"reason\":\"Access refused.\"}` and the container exited 1.\n\n**Fix:** One command:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified outcome:**\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` (no restarts on the new pod)\n- `/app` vhost has `app-queue` of type `classic` with 36+ messages accumulating\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are running and clustered\n- No NetworkPolicy was blocking traffic (none existed)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":503,"cache_read_input_tokens":34780,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":503},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a3f4f64f-a096-41fd-8558-1fe941707dc0","uuid":"d558febe-dd5f-45bb-b7d6-30ad40af733d","request_id":"req_011Ccc3DnWrKAmx98riWL1Sk"}
